{With 8 points, SOUTH is not strong enough to open the bidding.

NORTH has 13 points, barely meeting the minimum for a 1-opening. Note that the fifth and

sixth ♠ each added 1 point to his count. He opens 1♠.

Although SOUTH passed originally, she must respond to NORTH's opening bid. Since she has

three ♠s she raises to 2♠.

In light of SOUTH's weak response NORTH passes.}
